						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājēndra I. Year 21: 1032-33 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The title of the king <hi rend="italic">Pūrvadēśamum-gaṅgaiyum-kiḍāramum-koṇḍaruḷiya Para kēsari</hi> and palaeographical considerations suggest the identity of the king with Rājēndra I,</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of a <hi rend="italic">Śekaṇḍigai</hi> (gong) weighing 72 <hi rend="italic">palams</hi>, by Tiṇaiyaṉ Āḍavalāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi>••• Periyaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
